# RBAC Middleware (Zigo)

## Auth source

- **Not NextAuth/JWT middleware parsing.** Supabase SSR session (`supabase.auth.getUser()`) + `public.users.role`.
- Login entry: `/auth` (alias `/login` redirects here).

## Roles

PostgreSQL `user_role`: `teacher`, `parent`, `student`.

**Institution** is not a separate middleware role — institution accounts register as `teacher` with `organization_type` set. Teacher-only routes cover them.

## Protected path rules

Defined in `src/features/shared/middleware/role-guards.ts` (`ROLE_PATH_RULES`).

| Path prefix | Allowed roles |
| --- | --- |
| `/teacher`, `/dashboard/teacher`, `/create` | `teacher` |
| `/parent`, `/dashboard/parent`, `/family` | `parent` |
| `/student`, `/dashboard/student` | `student` |
| `/learn` | `student`, `parent` |
| `/avatar`, `/sparks` | `student` |
| `/store` | `student`, `parent` |

Shared routes (`/`, `/feed`, `/explore`, `/profile`, `/questions`) have no strict role prefix rule.

## Platform admin pages

`/admin` is **not** role-based — it requires `current_user_is_platform_admin` RPC.

After auth gate `ready`:

- Non-admin → redirect to role dashboard (`/teacher`, `/parent`, `/student`) or `/auth` if profile missing.
- Platform admin → allow (any `users.role`).

## Unauthorized behavior

After auth gate `ready`:

1. Wrong role for strict path → redirect to role dashboard (`/teacher`, `/parent`, `/student`).
2. `/dashboard/teacher` etc. → canonical redirect to `/teacher` then RBAC applies.
3. Unauthenticated protected page → `/auth?next=...`

API routes enforce RBAC separately via `requireAuthenticatedProfile()` + RLS.

Admin API (`/api/admin/*`) uses `withAdminApiHandler()` → `requirePlatformAdminAccess()` + standard `{ error, code }` responses. Prefix rules live in `src/features/shared/api/rbac.ts` (`API_RBAC_PREFIX_RULES`).

